lign=left class=m><span class=title> The Deposition of Gingerhopp Diggs</span><hr size=1> The Deposition of Gingerhopp Diggs<br>
<br>
Senior Agent Mumsley Thunderfoot Reporting<br>
<br>
<br>
It has been over a month since the horrifying capture of Sugarfoot Deeppockets in the Misty Thicket.  Unfortunately, up to this point there has been no further progress in the case.  With Sugarfoot Deeppockets at the time of her abduction was her close friend Gingerhopp Diggs.  Having gone into shock after the incident, her health was in a precarious state.  She has only now recovered and was able to prepare a deposition relating the details of the incident.  Following is a direct transcript of her testimony:<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
&quot;That night Sugar and I had left the Vale on a casual walk through the Thicket.  We were talking about.....about.....*begins to sob*.....boys and things of that sort.  Well you can imagine we wanted our privacy to discuss these things, and we all know how many prying ears there are within the Vale proper.<br>
<br>
&quot;Suddenly there was a terrifying voice behind us.  With a horrid, guttural accent, it boomed: 'You fixum bootses.  Sum halflin' bootses you fixum!'<br>
<br>
&quot;We both spun around quickly to see a gruesome sight.  A horrid, gigantic troll lumbering at least ten feet tall, staring down at us with hateful eyes.  We both screamed at the sight and I almost fainted myself.  'YOU MUST FIX OR WE EATS YOU!'<br>
<br>
&quot;The troll reached her hands out.  She was carrying some strange items, which I was too terrified to make out [note from reporting agent:  Gingerhopp Diggs was later able to recall a bit more but was puzzled that the items held by the troll were an odd assortment of baking supplies and footwear].  Sugar was a bit more collected than I and managed to say, 'I....haven't....I don't know!  Please....no!'<br>
<br>
&quot;At this the troll seemed outraged.  'You trickum Snarg.  You breaks tummyfoots.  Snogg hungry now for no more tummyfoots.  You fix tummyfoots or we EATS HALFLINSES!'  The terrible troll at this point reached out and grabbed poor, dear Sugar by the shoulders, lifting her into the air.  She was too terrified to struggle much.  It was horrible....simply DREAFUL.  My heart was pounding so quickly and I could scarcely breath, and then everything was spinning and I saw no more.&quot;<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
The deposition of Gingerhopp Diggs is now an invaluable lead in tracking down the culprit.  We now suspect a large female troll going by the name of Snarg.  Unfortunately, the testimony leads to very unfortunate circumstances regarding Sugarfoot Deeppockets.  We can only hope that she has somehow found a way to survive, but the expectations of the Leatherfoot Raiders agents assigned to the case are low.  Mac Deeppockets, after hearing the testimony, closed his eyes slowly and reached for the counter of his bar for support.  Afterward he closed the Fool's Gold early and asked to be left alone.<br>
<br>
We can only hope that the culprit will be obtained and justice will be served.  Several agents are following leads regarding the location of the missing troll, but even spies in Grobb report of never having heard of a &quot;Snarg.&quot;  There are a few other leads that are being followed at the moment, including the possibility that the name &quot;Snarg&quot; was not heard quite correctly and may be a different, but similar name.  The reference to &quot;tummyfoots&quot; is puzzling and currently under scrutiny.<br>
<br>
As further update, two more disappearances have been reported.  The first was ten days following the disappearance of Sugarfoot and the second nineteen days after.  In both cases the victims were vagrants living in the Thicket with no known relatives.<br>
<br>
Any further information on the matter will be duly reported. <p><img src="http://www.geocities.com/jubbernaut/images/mumsley2.jpg">
